STRONGHART COMPANY v. BANKERS’ THRIFT CORPORATION. STRONGHART COMPANY v. AMERICAN BADGE COMPANY. No. 4097. Circuit Court of Appeals, Seventh Circuit. Nov. 16, 1932. Miller Belfield, of Chicago, Ill., for appellant. Max W. Zabel, of Chicago, Ill., for appellee.

Before ALSCHULER and EVANS, Circuit Judges, and WILKERSON, District Judge.

PER CURIAM.

On motion of counsel for appellant, it is now here ordered, adjudged, and decreed by this court that this appeal be, and the same is- hereby, dismissed, with costs.
